Reasoning: The paper deals with centrality measures and their applications in various disciplines, which is a common topic in the field of social informatics (cs.SI). The paper also proposes an algorithm for efficient computation of betweenness centrality, which falls under the category of social network analysis (cs.SD) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The use of non-uniform node sampling model and analysis of Erdos-Renyi graphs suggests a focus on statistical analysis and modeling (cs.SY) and network inference (cs.NI).
